V2:

- Emit metrics, both from userspace and from
  eBPF maps. These should be fed into
  VictoriaMetrics
- A program's common options should also specify,
  (1) the version string, (2) whether the options
  are "initialised", (3) the iface the program is
  attached to
- Reconcile the RIB with the FIB, instead of only
  applying RIB updates and not diffing against
  the existing FIB state, this will require a
  blocking executor so we don't stargve Tokio
  threads
- Re-use maps on startup instead of clearing them
  out and creating new maps. To do this, we need
  to make sure we avoid re-using maps if the data
  sizes are incompatible
- Statically assert eBPF map sizes/other constants
  during compilation
- Ratelimit eBPF log tailing based on some
  configurable quota
- Attach erez_encap via the TCX datapath instead
  of using TC + qdiscs
- How to route across the backbone, do I do a
  custom implementation of MPLS?
- Collect BIRD and erezd logs from stderr and
  feed them into VictoriaLogs. We should emit wide
  events for the daemon
- Inject arbitrary latency into links, or affect
  their up/down state to simulate failure recovery
  during tests
- Decap should only act on packets which are
  destined for one of the router's next hops
- Encap/Decap should only act on packets if the
  userspace counter is constantly incremented
- Use distinct error values to indicate different
  types of errors, i.e. TTL too low vs. failed to
  read packet, errors for short reads?
- Liveness probes for each nextop, i.e. healthcheck
  that we can send probes and receive them back, if
  we can't then we stop using a nexthop
- Unit, integration, and E2E tests. We want to be
  able to trace the packet path through a topology
- Load balance against nexthops based on health, so
  we avoid sending traffic through nexthops which
  are full (bandwidth)/unhealthy/expensive etc.
- Parse the BIRD control protocol instead of parsing the
  stdout output
- Set up automatic clang formatting for C code in
  the codebase
